1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,068
Sure, sure, hanging around
like a duck in a shooting gallery.

2
00:00:00,274 --> 00:00:02,708
From the skylight, but
how did he reach the ground?

3
00:00:02,910 --> 00:00:06,903
- I'm pretending there ain't any Earl.
- He could have jumped to this roof.

4
00:00:07,114 --> 00:00:09,480
From the roof he could slide
down the drainpipe.

5
00:00:09,683 --> 00:00:11,446
And come in any of these windows.

6
00:00:11,652 --> 00:00:13,313
If the story walks in the window...

7
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:17,115
Masterminds. Why don't you go home?
Maybe Williams will call on you.

8
00:00:17,391 --> 00:00:19,359
It'd be funny if he was
in this building.

9
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:21,255
Why not search the building?

10
00:00:21,461 --> 00:00:24,760
- I am not wandering all over.
- A great bunch of reporters you are.

11
00:00:24,965 --> 00:00:27,126
Too lazy to go after
the biggest story in years.

12
00:00:27,334 --> 00:00:29,825
You seem pretty anxious
to get rid of us.

13
00:00:30,037 --> 00:00:32,631
- Are you trying to scoop us?
- Are you crazy? On my time?

14
00:00:32,839 --> 00:00:36,866
Maybe Mollie's been giving her
the truth on how Williams got the gun.

15
00:00:37,077 --> 00:00:38,101
I didn't do nothing.

16
00:00:38,312 --> 00:00:40,337
- Come clean.
- Let the girl alone. She's...

17
00:00:40,547 --> 00:00:41,775
Well?

18
00:00:41,982 --> 00:00:43,472
Mrs. Baldwin. Mother.

19
00:00:43,684 --> 00:00:47,518
Don't "mother" me. Playing cat and
mouse and keeping my boy locked up.

20
00:00:47,721 --> 00:00:50,554
Making us miss two trains, and you
supposed to be married tomorrow.

21
00:00:50,757 --> 00:00:54,249
- I'll be with you in five minutes...
- Just give me Bruce's money.

22
00:00:54,461 --> 00:00:57,919
You can stay here forever,
you and that murderer you caught.

23
00:00:58,131 --> 00:01:00,326
- Murderer?
- Which one of these men is it?

24
00:01:00,534 --> 00:01:03,298
- They all look like murderers.
- What murderer did you catch?

25
00:01:03,503 --> 00:01:05,403
I never said any such thing.

26
00:01:05,606 --> 00:01:08,166
I'm quoting my son.
He has never lied to me.

27
00:01:08,375 --> 00:01:09,375
Somebody's lying.

28
00:01:09,576 --> 00:01:11,976
- I never said anything like that.
- Yes, you did.

29
00:01:12,179 --> 00:01:14,613
I said I was trying
to find the murderer.

30
00:01:14,815 --> 00:01:16,806
- Quit stalling.
- She's got it balled up.

31
00:01:17,017 --> 00:01:18,609
Who are you holding out on?

32
00:01:18,819 --> 00:01:20,650
Nobody. Now let me go, will you?

33
00:01:21,088 --> 00:01:22,612
Stop it, stop it!

34
00:01:22,823 --> 00:01:26,816
She don't know where he is.
I'm the only one that knows.

35
00:01:27,027 --> 00:01:28,517
- Where's Williams?
- Try and find out.

36
00:01:28,729 --> 00:01:31,323
- Come on, talk.
- Now you want me to talk?

37
00:01:31,531 --> 00:01:33,158
- Talk.
- Ain't that funny?

38
00:01:33,367 --> 00:01:36,768
You wouldn't listen to me before,
and now you want me to talk.

39
00:01:36,970 --> 00:01:37,970
Don't say anything.

40
00:01:38,138 --> 00:01:39,901
- I know what I'm doing.
- Stay out of this.

41
00:01:40,107 --> 00:01:42,405
- Why didn't you listen to me?
- Cut that out.

42
00:01:42,609 --> 00:01:44,133
- Hands off!
- Where is he?

43
00:01:44,344 --> 00:01:47,836
Why do you want to know? So you can
write more lies to sell papers?

44
00:01:48,048 --> 00:01:51,848
- Never mind that.
- All right. I'll give you a story.

45
00:01:52,052 --> 00:01:53,110
A wonderful story!

46
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:57,051
Only this time it'll be true.
You'll never find me now!

47
00:01:57,457 --> 00:01:59,220
Get the ambulance, somebody!

48
00:01:59,426 --> 00:02:01,155
Get an ambulance, somebody!

49
00:02:04,831 --> 00:02:08,062
- She's dead.
- No, she isn't killed, she's moving!

50
00:02:12,472 --> 00:02:15,498
- Did you see that? She jumped.
- I know that.

51
00:02:15,709 --> 00:02:17,108
Where have you got Williams?

52
00:02:17,310 --> 00:02:19,335
Hidden. He's in the desk.

53
00:02:19,546 --> 00:02:20,843
She didn't kill herself.

54
00:02:21,048 --> 00:02:22,538
- How're you doing?
- Let me out.

55
00:02:22,749 --> 00:02:24,376
Quiet. You're sitting pretty.

56
00:02:24,584 --> 00:02:26,313
- What's in there?
- Who are you?

57
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:28,613
- This is Bruce's mother.
- What are you doing?

58
00:02:28,822 --> 00:02:30,881
- Shut up!
- You're doing something wrong.

59
00:02:31,091 --> 00:02:33,082
- Mother, please.
- Take her out of here.

60
00:02:33,293 --> 00:02:37,229
- Take the lady to Polack Mike's.
- My name's Louie Peluso.

61
00:02:38,999 --> 00:02:41,160
See that she doesn't talk to anyone.

62
00:02:41,368 --> 00:02:42,995
Tell them it's a case of D.T.'s.

63
00:02:43,203 --> 00:02:45,171
Don't worry, Mother.
It's only temporary.

64
00:02:45,672 --> 00:02:47,435
Let go of me.

65
00:02:48,075 --> 00:02:50,805
- Where are you going?
- To get Bruce out of jail.

66
00:02:51,011 --> 00:02:54,640
- Why did you do this to me?
- Get Bruce out of jail?

67
00:02:54,848 --> 00:02:58,181
How can you worry about a man
who's resting in a police station?

68
00:02:58,385 --> 00:03:01,411
- This is war! You can't desert me.
- Get off that trapeze.

69
00:03:01,621 --> 00:03:03,020
You've got your story.

70
00:03:03,223 --> 00:03:05,987
<i>"Earl Williams captured
by the Morning Post".</i>

71
00:03:06,193 --> 00:03:08,718
I covered your story for you,
now I'm getting out.

72
00:03:08,929 --> 00:03:13,525
You drooling idiot, there are 365 days
in a year one can get married.

73
00:03:13,734 --> 00:03:16,669
How many times you got a murderer
locked up in a desk?

74
00:03:16,870 --> 00:03:19,236
You got the whole city
by the seat of the pants.

75
00:03:19,439 --> 00:03:21,498
You've got the brain of a pancake.

76
00:03:21,708 --> 00:03:24,233
This isn't just a story.
It's a revolution.

77
00:03:24,444 --> 00:03:27,311
The greatest yarn since
Livingston discovered Stanley.

78
00:03:27,514 --> 00:03:31,177
- The other way around.
- Don't get technical at such a time.

79
00:03:31,384 --> 00:03:34,285
You've taken a city that's been
graft-ridden for 40 years...

80
00:03:34,488 --> 00:03:37,582
...and given us a chance to have
the same kind of government...

81
00:03:37,791 --> 00:03:39,349
...New York has under La Guardia.

82
00:03:39,559 --> 00:03:43,620
If I didn't have your best interest
at heart, I wouldn't argue with you.

83
00:03:43,830 --> 00:03:47,596
You've done something big.
You've stepped up into a new class.

84
00:03:47,801 --> 00:03:51,669
We'll make such monkeys of those
ward healers nobody'll vote for them.

85
00:03:51,872 --> 00:03:53,737
- Expose them?
- We'll crucify that mob.

86
00:03:53,940 --> 00:03:56,932
We'll keep Williams under cover,
until we can break the story...

87
00:03:57,144 --> 00:03:59,044
...then share the glory
with the governor.

88
00:03:59,246 --> 00:04:01,840
- I get it, I get it.
- You'll kick over City Hall.

89
00:04:02,048 --> 00:04:05,984
You got the mayor and Hartwell
backed up against the wall.

90
00:04:06,186 --> 00:04:09,019
This isn't just a newspaper story.
It's a career!

91
00:04:09,222 --> 00:04:12,419
And you bellyache about catching
the eight or nine o'clock train.

92
00:04:12,626 --> 00:04:16,323
- But I never figured it that way.
- Because you're a doll-faced hick.

93
00:04:16,530 --> 00:04:20,022
They'll be naming streets after you.
There'll be statues of you.

94
00:04:20,233 --> 00:04:23,396
The movies will be after you.
There'll be a Hildy Johnson cigar.

95
00:04:23,603 --> 00:04:26,902
I can see the billboards now:
"Light up with Hildy Johnson..."

96
00:04:27,107 --> 00:04:28,904
- We got a lot to do.
- Now you're talking.

97
00:04:29,109 --> 00:04:33,170
- We can't leave Williams here.
- We'll take him to my private office.

98
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:36,440
- How are you going to take him?
- We'll carry the desk over.

99
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:38,242
It's crawling with cops outside.

100
00:04:38,451 --> 00:04:40,646
We'll lower it out
the window with pulleys.

101
00:04:40,854 --> 00:04:42,583
Start pounding out a lead!

102
00:04:42,789 --> 00:04:46,748
- How much of this stuff do you want?
- All you the words you got.

103
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:50,293
- Can I call the mayor a bird of prey?
- Call him anything you like.

104
00:04:50,497 --> 00:04:54,558
Give him the works. Hello, Duffy?
We got the biggest story in years.

105
00:04:54,768 --> 00:04:58,135
<i>"Earl Williams captured by
the Morning Post. Exclusive!"</i>

106
00:04:58,338 --> 00:05:00,067
Tear out the whole front page.

107
00:05:00,273 --> 00:05:03,367
The whole front page. Out!
And never mind the European war.

108
00:05:03,577 --> 00:05:07,206
We got something bigger than that.
Hildy Johnson's writing the lead.

109
00:05:07,414 --> 00:05:09,314
And get hold of Butch O'Connor.

110
00:05:09,516 --> 00:05:11,746
Tell him to come up here
with his wrestlers.

111
00:05:11,952 --> 00:05:13,044
Yeah, Butch O'Connor.

112
00:05:13,253 --> 00:05:15,187
What? I've got a desk
I want moved...

113
00:05:15,388 --> 00:05:16,753
What the deuce do you want?

114
00:05:16,957 --> 00:05:18,117
- Hello, Bruce.
- Hildy.

115
00:05:18,325 --> 00:05:20,623
Never mind the Chinese earthquake.

116
00:05:20,827 --> 00:05:23,318
- I just want to ask you...
- How'd you get out of jail?

117
00:05:23,530 --> 00:05:25,259
Not through any help of yours.

118
00:05:25,465 --> 00:05:26,659
I'm not talking to you.

119
00:05:26,867 --> 00:05:31,065
I had to wire Albany for $100
so I could get out on bail.

120
00:05:31,638 --> 00:05:34,971
What will they think in Albany?
The money went to the police station.

121
00:05:35,175 --> 00:05:38,542
- We're waiting for that story.
- We'll explain everything to them.

122
00:05:38,745 --> 00:05:40,508
- Where's mother?
- She left.

123
00:05:40,714 --> 00:05:41,714
I can't hear you.

124
00:05:41,882 --> 00:05:43,372
- Where'd she go?
- Out someplace.

125
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:46,780
- Junk the Polish Corridor!
- Tell me where my mother was going.

126
00:05:46,987 --> 00:05:49,114
- She couldn't say.
- This is more important.

127
00:05:49,322 --> 00:05:51,654
- Did she get the money?
- She left in a hurry.

128
00:05:51,858 --> 00:05:53,519
- I'll take that money.
- In my purse.

129
00:05:53,727 --> 00:05:56,855
I can handle things.
I'll take that certified check too.

130
00:05:57,063 --> 00:06:00,499
I'll give you the tickets.
You'll find your money in the wallet.

131
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:02,964
My wallet? This is my wallet.

132
00:06:03,169 --> 00:06:06,070
Say, there's something funny going on...
What are you doing?

133
00:06:06,273 --> 00:06:08,173
Just wanted to look at it.

134
00:06:08,375 --> 00:06:10,070
Hildy, I'm taking...

135
00:06:10,777 --> 00:06:13,507
- I'm taking the 9 o'clock train.
- Sure, sure.

136
00:06:13,713 --> 00:06:17,046
Did you hear what I said?
I said I am taking the 9 o'clock...

137
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:19,081
Oh, Bruce, I put it in here!

138
00:06:21,121 --> 00:06:23,021
Let her alone, will you, buddy.

139
00:06:23,223 --> 00:06:25,748
- Do me a favor...
- Just answer one question.

140
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:27,927
You don't want to come
with me, do you?

141
00:06:28,128 --> 00:06:29,527
Answer me.
You don't, do you?

142
00:06:29,729 --> 00:06:32,323
No. Take the Miss America
pictures off page six.

143
00:06:32,532 --> 00:06:34,432
Hildy, tell me.
Tell me the truth.

144
00:06:34,634 --> 00:06:37,569
Wait a minute.
Now look here, my good man...

145
00:06:37,771 --> 00:06:39,432
You shut up, Burns.

146
00:06:39,639 --> 00:06:41,163
You're doing all this to her.

147
00:06:41,374 --> 00:06:43,365
She wanted to get away from you.

148
00:06:43,576 --> 00:06:45,601
But you caught her
and changed her mind...

149
00:06:45,812 --> 00:06:48,372
Stick Hitler on the funny page.
Now let me ask you...

150
00:06:48,581 --> 00:06:51,106
Will you give up everything
for a man like him?

151
00:06:51,318 --> 00:06:53,786
No, but something's happened.
I'll tell you...

152
00:06:53,987 --> 00:06:56,012
Tell him nothing.
He's a spy, you fool.

153
00:06:56,222 --> 00:06:57,553
- I am not a spy.
- Ridiculous.

154
00:06:57,757 --> 00:06:59,384
You're coming with me right now.

155
00:06:59,592 --> 00:07:02,254
Just a second. This is the
biggest thing in my life.

156
00:07:02,462 --> 00:07:05,329
I see. I'll keep.
I'm like something in the icebox.

157
00:07:05,532 --> 00:07:07,090
You just don't love me.

158
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:10,997
That isn't true. Just because you
won't listen you say I don't love you.

159
00:07:11,204 --> 00:07:14,173
You never intended to be decent
and live like a human being.

160
00:07:14,374 --> 00:07:17,138
All right, if that's what
you want to think.

161
00:07:17,344 --> 00:07:18,971
I'm trying to concentrate.

162
00:07:19,179 --> 00:07:22,410
- You're just like him and all the rest.
- Sure. That's what I am.

163
00:07:22,615 --> 00:07:25,812
What? Leave the rooster story alone.
That's human interest.

164
00:07:26,353 --> 00:07:28,412
If you had any sympathy
or understanding...

165
00:07:28,621 --> 00:07:30,589
- I understand, all right...
- Wait a minute.

166
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:34,817
There's one question I want to know.
The mayor's first wife's name.

167
00:07:35,028 --> 00:07:37,588
The one with the wart on her? Fanny.
What, Duffy?

168
00:07:37,797 --> 00:07:39,389
You never loved me at all.

169
00:07:39,599 --> 00:07:41,794
Never mind.
You don't work for advertising.

170
00:07:42,002 --> 00:07:44,800
If you change your mind,
I'm on the 9 o'clock train.

171
00:07:45,005 --> 00:07:47,974
If you want me, take me as I am.
Don't try to change me.

172
00:07:48,174 --> 00:07:50,734
I'm no suburban bridge player.
I'm a newspaperman.

173
00:07:50,944 --> 00:07:53,208
That's it. Keep it coming
as fast as you can.

174
00:07:53,413 --> 00:07:55,677
Get back in there, you mock turtle.

175
00:07:58,184 --> 00:08:00,000
You tell Butch it's a matter
of life and death?
